18
00:00:30,960 --> 00:00:31,160
Hurry!

19
00:00:32,780 --> 00:00:33,240
[SHOUTING]

20
00:00:47,320 --> 00:00:48,880
This wasn't in the plan.

21
00:00:49,700 --> 00:00:51,380
I was supposed to shoot Shuval.

22
00:00:52,000 --> 00:00:53,700
So how come there's a fire?

23
00:00:58,780 --> 00:01:02,560
I get it. You changed your mind, didn't you, Yo-Hai?

24
00:01:03,560 --> 00:01:06,080
This is better. Much better.

25
00:01:07,180 --> 00:01:12,140
They're running around like ants, bumping into each other, trying to get out, just like ants!

26
00:01:16,500 --> 00:01:20,340
Amazing. You're amazing, Yo-Hai. Amazing.

27
00:01:24,360 --> 00:01:25,100
(laughing)

28
00:01:30,850 --> 00:01:31,660
Come and watch.

29
00:01:32,430 --> 00:01:33,100
It's pretty.

30
00:01:46,180 --> 00:01:48,720
No, no, the books are burning.

31
00:01:53,760 --> 00:01:56,720
Everyone is running and falling over each other,

32
00:01:57,400 --> 00:01:59,800
without a thought for anyone but themselves.

33
00:02:02,900 --> 00:02:04,660
Can you sense it in the room?

34
00:02:05,880 --> 00:02:07,060
The fear.

35
00:02:51,980 --> 00:02:53,400
(dramatic music)

36
00:03:37,820 --> 00:03:42,840
Whether or not he is successful on his first kill, that's what it all comes down to.

37
00:03:44,000 --> 00:03:47,440
Remember, either he's got what it takes, or he doesn't.

38
00:03:50,260 --> 00:03:52,340
So, have you ever trained with a gun before?

39
00:03:52,660 --> 00:03:53,600
Uh, no.

40
00:03:53,980 --> 00:03:56,120
I guess that means that you're self-taught, then.

41
00:03:57,540 --> 00:03:59,680
Actually, I've never shot a gun before.

42
00:04:00,820 --> 00:04:02,480
What? You mean not even once?

43
00:04:02,880 --> 00:04:03,360
Right.

44
00:04:06,600 --> 00:04:08,180
Remember, two shots.

45
00:04:09,080 --> 00:04:12,180
Whenever you fire your gun, you always pull the trigger twice.

46
00:04:13,120 --> 00:04:15,380
It betters your chances of taking out your objective.

47
00:04:16,040 --> 00:04:19,560
If you can't do that, then you're as good as dead. It's all over.

48
00:04:28,380 --> 00:04:29,660
I have to shoot.

49
00:04:31,920 --> 00:04:33,760
You won't be able to do it.

50
00:04:34,140 --> 00:04:35,560
I have to shoot you.

51
00:04:36,540 --> 00:04:38,220
I'm sure you can't.

52
00:04:38,340 --> 00:04:39,500
I have to kill you.

53
00:04:39,700 --> 00:04:41,140
You're a doctor of medicine.

54
00:04:42,660 --> 00:04:45,940
And you've dedicated your career to saving life.

55
00:04:48,320 --> 00:04:51,500
Taking life is my job, and I do it well.

56
00:04:52,800 --> 00:04:54,620
Give it up. You can't do it.

57
00:05:06,540 --> 00:05:07,940
(grunting)

58
00:05:16,180 --> 00:05:17,800
- Remember, two shots.

59
00:05:18,460 --> 00:05:19,100
(gunshot)

60
00:05:20,560 --> 00:05:21,260
(screaming)

61
00:05:36,540 --> 00:05:36,740
[GUNSHOT]

62
00:05:40,400 --> 00:05:43,020
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

63
